name: Guardsman
description: A British guardsman, known as a foot guard. Wears a tall black hat with a yellow chin-strap. Must look straight ahead at all times, even when tourists attempt to distract them.

name: Guide Dog
description:
A guide (or Seeing Eye) dog, trained to help lead a person who is blind or visually impaired. Generally depicted as a yellowish-brown Labrador Retriever on all fours facing left, equipped with a harness and handle. Many platforms additionally include a collar.

Not to be confused with üêïü¶∫ Service Dog, though their popular applications may overlap.

Twitter implements the same dog as its üêï Dog. Samsung and Twitters guide dogs have green harnesses.

name: Guitar
description:
A guitar, which most platforms displayas a redelectric guitar.

Discontinued emoji sets or such asLG andHTC displayed this as an acoustic guitar, as did previousversionofWindows and Twemoji.

name: Hair Pick
description:
A hair pick with a handle and several long teeth. Used to style hair, especially thick, curly hair. May be used as a symbol of Black culture or Black pride.

May also be used to talk about grooming or self-care in general.

May be used metaphorically to refer to the verb comb, meaning to carefully search.

name: Haircut
description:
A person in the process of getting their hair cut, with scissors shown open next to the hair on their head.

While no gender is specified, many early designs displayed this emoji as a woman.

Windows previously displayed this emoji as a comb and scissors, instead of a person havingtheir hair cut.

name: Hamburger
description:
A burger with a beef patty, usually depicted on a sesame bun with cheese, lettuce, and tomatomaking it a cheeseburger, though officially called Hamburger by Unicode.

Platforms stack the ingredients in various orders. Google previously placed the cheese under the patty, acontroversyCEO Sundar Pichai addressed in 2018.

name: Hammer
description:
A claw hammer, as used for driving or removing nails. Generally depicted with a metal head and woodenhandle, positioned at a 45 angle with the head at the upper left.

Commonly used for content concerning tools, building, and construction as well as various senses of breaking or smashing. May also represent hard work or be applied to hammer-related expressions, e.g., nailed it.

Apple and Facebooks designs previously displayed a gavel, Softbanks a mallet. Not to be confused with ‚õèÔ∏èPick or ü™ìAxe.

name: Hammer and Pick
description:
A hammer and pick, as used for breaking up rocks in mining, crossed in an X shape. Generally depicted as metal, mallet- and chisel-styled hammers with wooden handles. The heads of the tools face up, with the pick usually at the right. Often used for various content concerning tools, building, and construction.

Facebook implements the same designs as for its üî®Hammer and ‚õèÔ∏èPick. Samsungs design previously featured stylized, white tools on a green square, as a sign or icon of a mine.

name: Hammer and Wrench
description:
A hammer and wrench, as kept in a toolbox, crossed in an X shape. Depicted with metal tools facing up, the hammer positioned at the upper left. Most vendors implement the same design as for their üî®Hammer and üîßWrench.

Commonly used for various content concerning tools, building, construction, and work, both manual and digital.

name: Hamsa
description:
A blue hand with an eye in the center of the palm.

The hamsa is an ancient symbol important to multiple religions including Islam, Judaism, Buddhism, and Christianity. It represents luck, protection, guidance, feminine power, and faith, among other meanings.

name: Hamster Face
description:
A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a hamstera small rodent often kept as a petlooking straight ahead. Generally depicted as a brown-and-white faced hamster with whiskers, a pink nose, puffy cheeks, and large, round, pink ears, sometimes with a buck tooth.

Often used with an affectionate tone. May be used to represent a gerbil, guinea pig, chinchilla, or related animals. Does not have a full-bodied hamster emoji counterpart.

Not to be confused with üê≠ Mouse Face.

Microsofts hamster was previously gray.

name: Hand with Index and Middle Fingers Crossed
description:
Afingers crossed emoji whichdisplaystheindex (first) finger crossed over themiddle (second)finger. Commonly used as a gesture indicatingluck, or to showdesire of a favorable outcome.

This emoji was previously displayed with an additional finger on Samsung devices.

name: Hand with Index Finger and Thumb Crossed
description:
A hand with the index finger and thumb crossed and the rest of the fingers making a fist. Can be used in various contextstorepresent the fingers snapping, love, or money.

In this emoji, the index finger and the thumb form a small heart shape. This gesture, used to express love or affection,is known as a finger heartand was popularized in the 2010s by South Korean celebrities, including actors, K-pop stars, and comedians.

The same gesture may be used in the context of money to indicate a luxury or an expensive item, a lack of money, or a request to be paid.

name: Handbag
description:
A bag or purse, used to carry personal items, often doubling as a fashion accessory.

The design of this emoji varies, with most platforms opting for leather-looking styles in brown or orange. Samsungs design used to be pink, but is now light brown. Twitters purple design stands out among the other platforms.

Not to be confused with the smaller and handleless pouch emoji sometimes referred to as üëù Clutch Bag.

name: Handball
description: A person playing the sport of handball, shown jumping in the air about to throw the ball. Apples design is shown wearing protective goggles.

name: Handshake
description:
Two hands performing a handshake gesture, indicating acordial greeting between friends or associates.

As of late 2021s Emoji 14.0 recommendations, this emoji design has multiple skin tone modifier options. Certain platforms did, however, support a small number of single skin tone options for the handshake emoji prior to 2021 (e.g. both Googleand Samsung in 2017).View all handshake emojis.

name: Happy Person Raising One Hand
description:
A person with itshand in the air, as if it wants to ask or answer a question.

Generally displayed as a woman, but is not defined as one particular gender.Previously showeda blob-like gender-inclusive characterin the Google artwork.

name: Hatching Chick
description:
A baby chicken (chick), hatching from an egg and seeing the world for the first time. Depicted as a yellow chick with an orange beak facing forward in the cracked, bottom half of a white egg, generally shown flapping its wings with a cute facial expression.

Often used with an affectionate tone. May be used to represent various types of baby birds. May also be used to representchicken foods (e.g., poultry, eggs), spring, Easter, or slang senses of chick.

Not to be confused with üê§ Baby Chick or üê•Front-Facing Baby Chick(out of its egg), though their applications overlap. See also üêî Chicken and üêì Rooster.

Twitter and Facebooks designs do not include wings. Googles design previously featured motion lines around the chicks wings, indicating flapping.Facebooks design previously showed part of the egg atop the chicks head.

name: Headphone
description:
Headphones, used to listen to music or other forms audio, such as podcasts.Most platforms display this emoji with large over-ear headphones in shades of black, blue, and gray.

Apple previously displayedthis emoji as iconic iPod white earbuds, followed by blackBeats headphones in 2016, and in 2021 switched to display white AirPods Max.

name: Headstone
description:
A headstone or tombstone, used to mark graves. Appearance varies from platform to platform, with different shapes and inscriptions.

Used to talk about death  literally, metaphorically, and metaphysically.

Often paired with other death-related emoji like ‚ö∞Ô∏è Coffin and ‚ò†Ô∏è Skull and Crossbones.

name: Health Worker
description: A person working in the field of health care. This may be used to represent a doctor, nurse, or pharmacist.

name: Hear-No-Evil Monkey
description:
The hear no evil monkey, called Kikazaru (Japanese for hear not), one of the Three Wise Monkeys. Depicted as the brown üêµ Monkey Face with hands covering its ears.

The Three Wise Monkeys represent the proverb see no evil, hear no evil, speak no evil, frequentlyinterpreted asa call for discretion or willful ignorance.

Often used as a playful way to convey I cant believe what Im hearing! or, more generally, to express astonishment or disbelief.

See also üôàSee-No-Evil Monkey and üôä Speak-No-Evil Monkey.

This emoji is considered racist in some contexts, particularly when used to disparage, insult, and abuse people with dark skin, especially Black people.

name: Heart Decoration
description:
A decorative heart that generally displays as a white heart-shaped cutout in a pink or purple roundrect.

Google previously displayed a pink heart with yellow dots around it, Samsungs was a pink patterned heart, and Microsofts had cornerstitches.

name: Heart Hands
description:
Two hands forming a heart shape. Used to express love and support.

This emoji currently showns the heart being made through two hands being curved into a C-shape with their thumbs touching. This is stereotypically referred to as the Millennial Hand Heart.

name: Heart on Fire
description: A heart shown on fire, for extreme or passionate forms of love or lust. Most representative ofdesire or lust, this emojimay also indicatea sense of burning a past love and moving on.

name: Heart with Arrow
description:
A heart emoji with an arrow through the center, like the arrow that cupid shoots for love.

This emoji tends to spike in popularity on Valentines Day.

name: Heart with Ribbon
description: A heart-shaped box, tied with a ribbon. May be a gift box, box of chocolates, or a jewellery box.

name: Heavy Black Heart
description:
A classic red love heart emoji.

The red heart ideographis traditionally used for expressions of love and romance across many cultures, with this being amongst the most frequence use cases for this emoji.

However, the Red Heart emoji is also often used to express non-romantic positive sentiments, in part thanks to its use as one of the default reaction emoji options across many social messaging platforms (e.g. Instagram, Slack, WhatsApp).

This is historicallythe most popular heart emojiby a considerable distance and is amongst the most popular emojis of all time.

A similaremoji existsfor theheart suit in a deck of playing cards.

On Snapchat, this emoji displays next to a friendwhen you have been #1 BFs with each other for two consecutive weeks.

Note: the Unicode Character Database (UCD)name Heavy Black Heartpre-dates color emoji, when the term referred to a solid, black ‚ù§Ô∏é heart character. See the glossary for information on the termblack in historic Unicode character names.

description: A large division symbol, as used in mathematics.

name: Heavy Dollar Sign
description: A large dollar sign ($), which can be used to represent various international currencies. Generally depicted in either black or green.

name: Heavy Equals Sign
description: An equals sign in the style of the already existing set of mathematical symbols ‚úñÔ∏è Multiply, ‚ûï Plus, ‚ûñ Minus, and ‚ûó Divide.

name: Heavy Exclamation Mark Symbol
description: A large red exclamation mark (!) symbol emoji.

name: heavy-heart-exclamation
description: Learn about the heavy-heart-exclamation emoji ‚ù£. Find meanings, shortcodes, and usage information.

name: Heavy Heart Exclamation Mark Ornament
description: A decorativeexclamation mark, where a heart forms the top part of the symbol, and a circle the lower part. Similar to the way to the man in business suit levitatingalso creates a similar shape.

name: Heavy Large Circle
description: Used as an alternative to a check (tick) in Japan for a something that is correct. The opposite of an X (cross mark) for something wrong.

name: Heavy Minus Sign
description: A large minus symbol, as used in mathematics.

name: heavy-multiplication-x
description: Learn about the heavy-multiplication-x emoji ‚úñ. Find meanings, shortcodes, and usage information.

name: Heavy Plus Sign
description: A large plus / addition symbol, as used in mathematics.

name: Hedgehog
description:
A hedgehog. Asmall, spiny mammal sometimes kept as a pet. Generally depicted in full profile on all fours facing left, with a round, brown body covered with spines anda light-brown face and underside.

Sometimes used to represent a porcupine or echidna.

Twitters design has always been a hedgehog facing forward. Googles design originally featured a hedgehog facing forward, though it was changed to full profile with Android 11.0. Facebooks design previously featured a hedgehogon its back, rolled up in a ball.

name: Helicopter
description: A helicopter, which can hover in the air. Often seen in emergency circumstances such as transporting patients to a hospital, or for policeor fire-fightingactivity.

name: Helmet with White Cross
description:
A construction helmet, which is worn by the construction worker emoji in some emoji sets.

The cross on the helmet (shown in the Appleversion of this emoji) is used in Japan as a safety reminder inconstructionzones. It is also commonly seen on theMethelmet in the gameMega Man.

name: Herb
description:
An herb, a plant used in cooking or medicine. Depicted as a green sprig, as of basil, sage, or oregano, generally with five or seven leaves.

May be used for various content concerning cooking, herbal medicine, and plant life more generally. Occasionally used as slang for marijuana.

Not to be confused with üå± Seedling, though their applications may overlap.

name: Hibiscus
description:
A pink hibiscus, a flower that grows in warm climates. Depicted as a single, deep-pink hibiscus flower with green leaves and prominent, yellow stamen.

Commonly used for Valentines Day, Mothers Day, and other special occasions. May be more generally used to convey such ideasas love, happiness, and beauty. Also used as a pinkaccent color and in association with Hawaiiand other Polynesian places and cultures.

Google and Samsungs hibiscus flowers werepreviouslyorange.

name: High Brightness Symbol
description: An icon of a outlined sun, used when increasing¬†the brightness of a screen. Appears larger than the¬†Low Brightness Symbol.

name: High-Heeled Shoe
description:
A high-heeled shoe, primarily worn bywomen. Generally found in a context which requires formal dress, suchassocial occasions, or some work places.

Displayed in red on most platforms, though the color may vary.

name: High-Speed Train
description: A high speed train, designed to cover long distances at high speed.

name: High-Speed Train with Bullet Nose
description: A high speed train, designed to cover long distances at high speed. Also features a streamlined bullet nose, often used in reference to the Shinkansen in Japan.

name: High Voltage Sign
description:
A symbol for high voltage, as warns against injury from electricity. Depicted as a jagged yellow bolt.

Commonly used to represent lightning, electricity, and various flashes. Also used to represent metaphorical energy and signal attention online.

Samsungs bolt was previously white on a blue square, as an icon for high voltage.

name: Hiking Boot
description: A style of boot commonly worn on long walks or for hiking. Generally distinct from other footwear-related emojis by the considerable grip on the sole of the shoe.

name: Hindu Temple
description: A Hindu temple or mandir;a place of worship for followers of Hinduism. Depicted on most platforms as a red, orange, or golden building with a tall spire.

name: Hippopotamus
description:
A hippopotamus, a squatwater mammal with huge jaws. Generally depicted in gray or tan in full profile facing left.

Googles design used tofeaturea purple, cartoon-styled hippopotamus face. Facebooks hippopotamus is opening massive jaws, revealing tusks.

name: Hocho
description:
A knife with a long steel blade, as a chef uses to slice meat or vegetables. Depicted with a black or brown handle and positioned at a 45 angle, often with its point at the lower right.

May be used for content concerning cooking and food preparation, but often represents various senses of cutting and stabbing.Its Unicode name, Hocho, means kitchen knife in Japanese and refers to a variety of knives used in Japan.

Not to be confused with üó°Ô∏èDagger or ‚öîÔ∏èCrossed Swords.

name: Hole
description: A round, black, cartoon-styled hole, as a manhole or a hole (cup) in golf. May be used to represent various types of literal or figurative holes, e.g., black holes, rabbit holes.

name: Honey Pot
description:
A golden-yellow potof honey, as made bybeesand desired bybears. Shown with the sweet substance oozing down its sides, often with a honey dipper inside the small vessel.

May be used figuratively, as the term of endearment honey.

name: Honeybee
description:
A honey bee, a busy, flying insect that lives in a hive and makes honey. Depicted as a black-and-yellow bee with clear or white wings and a stinger.Variously facing left in full profile or shown from above.

May be used to represent various types of bees (e.g., bumblebee) and wasps (e.g., hornets, yellow jackets). May also be used to accent black-and-yellow colors or patterns. Popularly used in connection with singer and superstar Beyonc (nicknamed Queen Bey) or for metaphorical queen bees. Can also be used to refer to the city of Manchester in the United Kingdom, as the worker bee is the symbol of the city.

name: Hook
description:
A gold or silver hook. Can be used to represent literal hooks like the kinds you use to crochet or catch fish.

Also use metaphorically to talk about boxing or punching, music (the catchy part of a song), or in phrases like hook me up, hook up,getting hooked (on something), or hook, line, and sinker.

name: Horizontal Traffic Light
description:
A set of red, orange (amber) and green traffic lights, used at intersections. Less¬†common than the¬†vertical¬†traffic light.
Similar in appearance to the¬†traffic light controls in the upper-left of every OS X windows.

name: Horse
description:
A horse, a hoofed mammal used for riding and racing. Depicted as a brown horse in full profile galloping to the left, with a dark, flowing mane and tail.

May be used to represent various types of horses and their metaphorical senses (e.g., mustang, stallion).

May also be used as a compliment to an attractive person.

One of the 12 animals of the Chinese zodiac.a

Not to be confused with üê¥ Horse Face, üé† Carousel Horse, and üèá Horse Racing, which features a jockey on its back.

Apples horse is wearing a green saddle blanket, Facebooks a blue blanket with saddle. SoftBanks design previously featured a racing horse with a jockey.

name: Horse Face
description:
The face of a horse, generally facing left. Depicted as a light or reddish-brown horse with a dark brown or black mane, and, on many platforms, a light-colored muzzle.

Not to be confused with the full-bodied üêé Horse or üèá Horse Racing, though their applications may overlap. Some vendors implement asimilar design in ü¶Ñ Unicorn Face and ü¶ì Zebra.

WhatsApps horse is facing left, as Facebooks previously was. Microsofts horse was previously looking straight ahead, as was Samsungs, shown with a goofy, full-toothed grin. Softbank previously featured a full-bodied horse.

name: Horse Racing
description: Ajockey riding a horsein a horse race. Shown riding to the left of screen on all major platforms. Emoji modifiers change the skin tone of the jockey on some platforms, which can be difficult to discern at small sizes.

name: Hospital
description: A place where people are taken to receive medical care. This hospital has a large red cross on the front, often used as a symbol for health care.

name: Hot Beverage
description:
A cup of a steaming-hot beverage, usually taken as coffee ortea. Sometimes shown on a saucer.

Samsungs design previously featureda foamy-white tulip latte art design.

May be paired with theFrog Faceto represent the snarkyBut Thats None of My Business meme. Relatedly, can also be used alone to representtea as per the slang phrase spill the tea,used to request the sharing of gossip,news, or personal information. More recently, it can also be used to refer to a persons physical attractiveness, as per the slang phrase your body is tea.

name: Hot Dog
description: The cooked sausage of a hot dog in a slicedbunand drizzled with yellow mustard, as eaten at abaseballgame.

name: Hot Pepper
description: A bright redMexicanchili pepper, slightly curled and with a green stem. May be used to represent something hot and spicy, figuratively or literally, as adishon a restaurant menu.

name: Hot Springs
description: Representation ofhot springs with steam risingfrom a circular tub. This is the common symbol used to represent an onsen on maps inJapan.

name: Hotel
description:
A hotel building,displayed on most platforms as a building with many windows and a letter H on the front.

Can be easily confused with the Love Hotel, or Hospital emoji.Microsoft previouslydepicted this emoji as abed.

name: Hourglass
description:
A classic hourglass, all of its sand having flowed into the bottom bulb. Indicates time has passed. Color varies across platforms.

Commonly used for various content concerning time. May also be used for hourglass-shaped figures. Not to be confused with ‚è≥Hourglass Not Done, whose sand is still flowing.

Used on Snapchat to indicate a Snapstreak is soon to end.

name: Hourglass with Flowing Sand
description:
A classic hourglass, its sand still flowing from the top to bottom bulb. Indicates time is still passingbut life is short. Color varies across platforms.

Commonly used for various content concerning time. May also be used for hourglass-shaped figures. Not to be confused with ‚åõHourglass Done, whose sand has stopped flowing.

name: House Building
description:
A house, otherwise known as a home when someone is living in it. Suitable for a couple or larger family, other perhaps housemates.

Distinct from an apartment building due to its detached form, this house is likely in the suburbs of a city or arural area.

name: House Buildings
description: Multiple houses.

name: House with Garden
description: A suburban-looking house, witha tree, flower, or shrubs around it in the garden.

name: Hugging Face
description:
A yellow face smiling with open hands, as if giving a hug.May be used to offer thanks and support, show love and care, or express warm, positive feelings more generally.

Due to its hand gesture, often used to represent jazz hands, indicating such feelings as excitement, enthusiasm, or a sense of flourish or accomplishment.

Joins ü§îThinking Face, ü§´Shushing Face, and ü§≠Face With Hand Over Mouth as one of the few smileys featuring hands. For a more obvious hug, seeü´Ç People Hugging(new in 2020).

name: Hundred Points Symbol
description:
100 emoji: the number one-hundred, written in red, underlined twice for emphasis.

Originating from the number 100written on a school exam or paperto indicate a perfect scoreof 100 out of 100. Teachers in Japan mayalsouse a stampin addition to the 100 mark, to indicatethat a student has performed very well.

This 100emojiis commonly used as a shorthand for 100%, with the usage meaning keep it real or a similar sentiment. A 100 emoji can be used to express pride or general acceptance of an idea.

In Snapchat, the 100 emoji appearing next to a fire emoji indicates a 100 day Snapstreak.

name: Hushed Face
description:
A yellow face with small, open eyes, raised eyebrows, and a small,open mouth, as if it has been hushed by concern or correction. Meaning widely varies, but its expression is commonly taken as surprise, embarrassment, or mildexcitement.

Similar to üò≤Astonished Face, which features larger eyes and mouth.Google previously interpreted hushed as silenced,depictingthe emoji with a zipper mouth until Android 6.0.1. An earlyMicrosoftdesign featured a face with closed eyes and a flat, closed mouth.

name: Hut
description: A round hut with a thatched roof. Used to talk about huts, cottages, yurts, or homes in general.

name: Hyacinth
description:
A hyacinth with purple blossoms anda green stem.

Can be used to talk about the actual flower, flowers in general, or the color purple. Can also be usedin reference to springtime. May be used as part of the symbolic table setting for Nowruz, the Persian New Year.

name: I Love You Hand Sign
description: The gesture forI love youin American Sign Language, shown as a raised pinky (little) finger, index finger, and an extended thumb.

name: Ice Cream
description: One or more scoops of ice cream in a dessert bowl, variously topped with sprinkles, wafer rolls, orcherryand syrup. Flavors vary from vanilla,chocolate, and/orstrawberryacross platforms.

name: Ice Cube
description: A blue cube of ice. Can be used to talk about ice or cold temperatures in general. This emoji can also be used metaphorically to talk about something that is cool or chill.

name: Ice Hockey Stick and Puck
description: A hockey stick and puck, used in the sport of ice hockey. Not to be confused with the field hockey stick and ball.

name: Ice Skate
description:
A single ice skate used for ice skating. Shown in white andfacingrighton most platforms.

In the sport of figure skating, a white ice skate is traditionally worn by women, and a black ice skate worn by men. This emoji doesnt define the color to be used, but no major vendor currently displays this as black.

name: Identification Card
description: An identification card with a portrait and words. May be used to remind people to bring or show an id. May also be used in the context of a fake id.

name: Imp
description:
A face, usually purple, with two devil horns, frowning mouth and eyes, and eyebrows scrunched downwards in anger. Bears the same expression as üò†Angry Face and üò°Pouting Face on most platforms. Googles design is red and Facebooks has black horns, green eyes, and clenched teeth.

Its Unicode name, Imp, alludes to a small demon in folklore, though the smiley is commonly used to represent devils and devilish behavior, especially around Halloween. It is also used to convey various sentiments of anger or ideas of evil. More menacing than its counterpart, üòàSmiling Face With Horns.

Samsung previously depicted a childlike character with red hair and horns, fangs, and black wings. Earlier designs from Google featured an orangish-red character with blue hair and wings.

name: Inbox Tray
description:
A paper tray with a down arrow on top, as a symbol for an email inbox. Generally depicted as a white or wooden try with a red arrow. Samsung and Twittersarrows aregreen,WhatsApps gray.

May be used for various digital activity, including downloading, messaging, and emailing.

Facebooks design contains paper, as did an earlierGoogledesign.

See also üì§ Outbox Tray.

name: Incoming Envelope
description:
The back of an envelope, shown coming into an inbox or arriving with motion lines.

Commonly used as an icon for an email address. May also represent posting mail or sending messages more generally.

Apple and WhatsApps designs include an inbox tray. Facebooks designs feature a yellow envelope angled forward and trailed by three, blue lines, indicating sending. Googles design also previously displayed as a yellowenvelope.

Apples design previously featured three red motion lines, Microsofts a rightwards arrow.

name: Index Pointing at the Viewer
description:
A hand with the index finger pointing straight forward at the person viewing the emoji. Used to represent the word and concept of you, the second-person singular and plural pronoun.

This symbol is seen in art, advertisements, and military recruitment posters as a way to draw the viewer into the image theyre looking at.

This hand shape is also used in multiple sign languages from around the world.

name: Information Desk Person
description:
A person tipping their hand by their shoulder as if theyre carrying a tray of drinks or flipping their hair. Originally called Information Desk Person.

This emoji is commonly used to express sassiness or sarcasm.

While no gender is specified, many early designsdisplayed this emoji as a woman. Googles 2014 design shows a blob wearing white gloves and a pillbox hat. Microsofts 2015 design shows a woman doing this gesture while winking, a facial expression that further reinforces the sassy and sarcastic uses of this emoji.

name: Information Source
description:
A lowercase letteri, enclosed in a rounded square or circle. Implemented in apps orwebsitestoindicate that help or further information is available.

May be used as alogo for tourist information signage in a town or city.

description: A symbol showing the capitallettersA, B, Cand D. Intended to be used on a software keyboard, or other input screen totoggle capital letter input.

name: Izakaya Lantern
description:
A red paper lantern, as hangs outside an izakaya, a Japanese bar that serves drinks and casual food. Generally depicted as cylindrical with a black top and base and soft, orange glow.

May be used to represent various lights and lanterns as well as for its red color.

name: Jack-O-Lantern
description: An orange pumpkin carved into the shape of a face and commonly known as a Jack-o-lantern. See also Halloween.

name: Japanese Castle
description: A traditional Japanese Castle (Âüé, shiro or j≈ç), usually made from stone and wood.

name: Japanese Dolls
description:
Ornamental Japanese Emperor and Empress dolls, as displayed in celebration of Hinamatsuri on March 3 in Japan (Girls or Dolls Day).

Generally depicted as a Japanese Emperor (left, in blue, holding a scepter) and Empress (right, in red, holding a fan) in ceremonial court dress and seated on a tatami.

When not applied to Hinamatsuri, sometimes used to represent Japan, dolls, a pair of people (as a couple or two friends), and for various idiosyncratic purposes.

name: Japanese Goblin
description:
A menacing, red mask featuring a grotesquely long nose, angry eyes, and bushy eyebrows and mustache. Depicts a tengu, a proud trickster figure in Japanese folklore.

May popularly denote evil, anger, cruel or mischievous behavior, and sexual suggestion, due to the phallic appearance of its nose. May also represent supernatural or figurative trolls, goblins, and other such beings.

name: Japanese Ogre
description:
A grotesque, red face with horns, wide eyes, a large nose, crooked fangs, and a fringe of shaggy hair. Depicts an oni, a kind of hideous ogre in Japanese folklore.

On New Years Eve in some parts of Japan, men may wearoni masks and straw coats to dress up as namahage, another mythic being,to chide naughty children or ward off evil. May popularly denote supernatural or figurative beasts and demons.

A Japanesepost office, featuring the „Äí Japanese postal mark on the front of the building.

Microsofts design previouslydisplayed this mark on its owninstead of being featured on the building.

description:
A yellow and green shield symbol, called aShoshinsha Mark. Must be displayed by drivers in Japan for one year after they receive their drivers licence.

Similar to L-Platesused to identify learner drivers in other countries.

name: Jar

An empty glass jar.

May be used to talk about jars or anything that comes in jars, from pickles to condiments to jellies to sauces.

name: Jellyfish

name: Jigsaw Puzzle Piece
description:
A single piece of a jigsaw puzzle, shown with two tabs and two blanks.

Usually shown as a plain green puzzle piece, though color and imagery does vary.

name: Joystick
description:
A joystick, as used in playing classic arcade, computer, or video games. Generally depicted with a black base, red-knobbed control stick, and one or more red buttons.

Commonly used for content concerning various types of gaming; occasionaly applied to aviation and aircraft.

Googles base was previouslyblue, andMicrosoft previously featured a more modern design.

name: Judge
description: A person who presides over court proceedings, wearing the traditional black gown and wielding agavel.

name: Juggling
description:
A person juggling between three and five colored balls. The person shown in this emoji wears a hat on most major platforms.

Early Twitter and Facebook designs previously displayed this emoji as a pair of disembodied hands juggling threecolored balls.

name: Kaaba
description: A cube-shaped building located at the centre of the Al-Masjid al-Haram Mosque in Mecca.

name: Kangaroo
description:
A kangaroo, a marsupial with a large tail and legs. Depicted in yellowish-brown in full profile facing left with large, pointed ears, shown either resting on its hind legs and tail or jumping.

Commonly used in connection with Australia, where the animal is found.

name: Key
description:
A key, as opens a door or lock. Depicted at a 45 angle as a gold, bronze, or copper key with a round head and notched blade. Commonly used for figurative senses of key, e.g., the key to success, being key(crucial).

DJ Khaleduses the emoji to indicate hisSnapchat stories are official (verified). Apples design previously resembled a gold üóùÔ∏è Old Key, which emoji has similar applications.

May also represent digital keys in public-key technology. This may explain why the emojidoes not display in page titlesonApples Safari web browser, presumably to prevent less reputable sites from pretending to be secure (encrypted usingHTTPS).

description:
A keyboard, as used to type on a computer. Generally depicted as a gray device with white or black keys. Used for various content concerning computers, typing, and writing.

Apples design resembles the companys Magic Keyboard. Microsofts design was previouslyblue.

Not to be confused with üéπ Musical Keyboard.

name: Kiss
description:
A kissing gesture, shownwith a pink love heart floating in the air between two people.No gender is specified for the two people, and as such this may be used to represent the concept of a couple broadly, and/or as a means of showing two non-binary people.

Previously shown with the same appearance asüë©‚ù§Ô∏èüíãüë®Kiss: Woman, Man, but now displaystwo people with an ambiguous genderappearance.

name: Kiss Mark
description: The mark left after a firm kiss is placed with bright lipstick. Used in place of xxx (kisses), or to send a kiss to someone. More seductive than the kissemoji.

description: Two men displayed kissing, or gesturing a kiss toward each other.At small sizes this may be difficult to discern from the two women kissing.

name: Kiss: Woman, Man
description: A woman and a man displayed kissing, or gesturing a kiss toward each other.

name: Kiss: Woman, Woman
description: Two women displayed kissing, or gesturing a kiss toward each other. At small sizes this may be difficult to discern fromtwo men kissing.

name: Kissing Cat Face with Closed Eyes
description: A cartoon cat variant of üòö Kissing Face With Closed Eyes. Depicted as yellow on major platforms.

name: Kissing Face
description:
A yellow face with simple, open eyes and puckered lips giving a kiss. Commonly conveys sentiments of love and affection.

Like üòô Kissing Face With Smiling Eyes, this emoji is sometimes taken to represent whistling, especially when paired with a musical note. May convey such feelings as surprise, admiration, contempt, or feigned innocence, as a person casually whistling after wrongdoing saying,Nothing to look at here.

Similar to üòô Kissing Face With Smiling Eyes and üòöKissing Face With Closed Eyes but with less intimate eyes.

name: Kissing Face with Closed Eyes
description:
A yellow face with smiling eyes, rosy cheeks, and puckered lips giving a kiss. Commonly conveys sentiments of romantic love and affection. Several platforms, including Apple, feature the same eyes and cheeks as their ‚ò∫Ô∏èSmiling Face.

With its closed eyes, features an expression more intimate than üòôKissing Face With Smiling Eyess and üòóKissing Faces.

This emoji has a cat variant, üòΩKissing Cat Face.

name: Kissing Face with Smiling Eyes
description:
A yellow face with smiling eyes and puckered lips giving a kiss. Commonly conveys sentiments of love and affection.

Like üòóKissing Face, this emoji is sometimes taken to represent whistling, especially when paired with a musical note. May convey such feelings as surprise, admiration, contempt, or feigned innocence, as a person with hands in pocket casually whistling after wrongdoing, as ifsayingNothing to look at here.

With its smiling eyes, this emoji generally features an expression fonder than üòóKissing Facesbut less intimate than üòöKissing Face With Closed Eyess. Expect for onHuawei devices, where this emojis lips are plump and red like theüíãKiss Mark emoji.

name: Kite
description:
A kite. Usually diamond-shaped with a tail, this emoji appears in various colors across platforms.

Unlike other vendors, Huaweis design is shaped like a bird of prey.

name: Kiwifruit
description:
A kiwifruit, or Chinese gooseberry, with its fuzzy, brown skin sliced open to show its light-green flesh, white core, and black seeds.

May be associated withNew Zealand, whose residents are nicknamed Kiwis, after the bird.

name: Kneeling Person
description: A person kneeling down on one or both knees. May be used to represent someone in prayer, or aperson resting on the floor.

name: Knot
description:
Brightly colored rope forming a knot. Knot type varies across platform, with most designs showing a square knot, a figure eight knot, or a carrick bend. Samsungs design appears to be a carrick bend, but upon closer inspection, it is not correctly tied and would fall apart with a gentle tug.

Used to talk about rope or knots in general. Sometimes used in the context of marriage alongside the idiom tying the knot.Also used in the kink community to talk about bondage. May be used as a stand-in for the word notin emoji rebus puzzles.

name: Koala
description:
A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a koalaa bear-like marsupial known for eating eucalyptus and sleepinglooking straight ahead. Depicted as a gray face with round, fluffy ears and a large, black nose.

Often used with an affectionate tone and in association with Australia, where the animal is found.

Available as an Apple Animoji.

Googlepreviouslydepicted a full-bodied koala climbing a tree, Softbanks koalapreviouslyhad brown fur.

name: Lab Coat
description: A white coat worn in a science laboratory.

name: Label
description:
A light-brown or yellow rectangular tag, as labelled and attached to a key. Depictedat various anglespunched with a hole, generally with a metal ring or loop of string.

Commonly used to represent a price tag or metadata tag as well as for various senses of label.

WhatsApps is white.Apple removedits ring from earlierdesigns. Samsung previously featured the easter egg initials HMJ,whileGoogles design previouslyfeaturedtwo tags.

name: Lacrosse Stick and Ball
description: A stick and ball used in the sport oflacrosse. The ball is usually depicted as either orange or white, while the sticks color varies across emoji designs.

name: Ladder
description:
A wooden ladder with four or five rungs.

Used to represent ladders or the action of climbing. Also used metaphorically to represent systems through which you can climb, for example the corporate ladder or social ladder.

name: Lady Beetle
description:
A ladybug (ladybird, lady beetle), a beetle with a round, red shell with black spots. Generally depicted as a seven- or nine-spotted ladybug shown from above on its six legs, with antennae and itsdistinctively red-and-black, halved shell.

May be used a symbol of good luck.

Facebooks ladybug is shown on its legs facing forward.

name: Large Blue Circle
description: A circle shown in the color of blue. May be used to represent anything blue.

name: Large Blue Diamond
description:
A large version of the small blue diamond emoji.

Note: this emoji is not supported in Twitter / X names,to minimize confusion with a verified checkmark. Learn more here.

description: A square shown in the colorofblue. May be used to represent anything blue.

description: A circle shown in the color of brown. May be used to represent anything brown.

description: A circle shown in the color of green. May be used to represent anything green.

A square shown in the colorof green. May be used to represent anything green.

May 2021: Sometimes shown in Twitter names in support ofTaproot, aBitcoin fork (potential feature change) that would allow additional privacy measures for transactions.

description: A circle shown in the color of orange. May be used to represent anything orange.

name: Large Orange Diamond
description: A larger version of the small orange diamond emoji.

name: Large Orange Square
description: A square shown in the colorof orange. May be used to represent anything orange.

description: A circle shown in the color of purple. May be used to represent anything purple.

name: Large Purple Square
description: A square shown in the colorof purple. May be used to represent anything purple.

name: Large Red Circle
description: A circle shown in the color of red. May be used to represent anything red.

name: Large Yellow Circle
description: A circle shown in the color of yellow. May be used to represent anything yellow.

name: Large Yellow Square
description: A square shown in the color yellow. May be used to represent anything yellow, including a yellow penalty cardin football (soccer).

name: Last Quarter Moon Symbol
description:
A last quarter moon, the seventh of the eight phases of the moon. Depicts the moon as a cratered disc, its left side half illuminated in gold or silver, its remainder dark.

May be used to represent the moon more generally, nighttime, outer space, and astronomy. May also be used to convey enchanting or eerie feelings.

See also üåúLast Quarter Moon Face. Not to be confused with üåìFirst Quarter Moon, though their applications may overlap. Used as part of the Moon Emoji Creep meme.

Samsungs design once resembled a full moon with stars and previously displayed as a last quarter moon in a night sky with stars.

name: Last Quarter Moon with Face
description:
A last quarter moon with a human face, as the Man in the Moon. Generally depicts a wide, golden crescent moon with the profile of slightly smiling human face with a nose, facing right.

May be used to represent the moon more generally and saying good night.

See also üåóLast Quarter Moon and üåô Crescent Moon.Not to be confused withüåõFirst Quarter Moon Face, though their applications may overlap.

WhatsApps eyes are looking back. Facebooks moon is silver but was previously golden; Twitters was previously silver. Googles eyes were previously closed.

name: Latin Cross
description: A latin cross, otherwise known as a Christian cross. This cross symbol is often used as a symbol of Christianity. Similar in appearanceto the Orthodox cross.

name: Leaf Fluttering in Wind
description:
Leaves, as fluttering in a spring or summer breeze. Depicted as one or two green, almond-shaped leaves, with gray or blue motion lines, as if swirling in the air or as the wind blowing through the trees.

May be used to represent the season of fall/autumn, trees, and nature more generally.

name: Lion Face
description:
A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a lionthe large cat and king of the junglelooking straight ahead. Depicted as a golden-yellow lion face with a light- or dark-brown mane, white muzzle, and neutral expression.

Often used with an affectionate tone. Does not have a full-bodied lion emoji counterpart. A lion is represented as ‚ôå Leo in the Western zodiac.

Available as an AppleAnimoji.

Apples lion previously featured a timid-looking expression.

name: Lizard

A lizard, a scaly reptile with a long tail. Depicted as a light-green lizard on all fours from above, generally looking left with large eyes, a lightly textured or colored back, and toes outspread, as a gecko.

May be used for a variety of wild and pet lizards.

Googles lizard was previously brown.

name: Llama
description:
A llama, a long-necked, camel-like animal, native to South America andused for transport and wool. Depicted as a shaggy white, light-brown, or multicolored llama in full profile on all fours facing left.

May be used to represent an alpaca or related animals.

name: Lobster

A lobster, a large crustacean with a prominent tail and pincers. Depicted as a reddish-orange lobster (as cooked) from above, with a long body and tail, short, tentacle-like eyes, and ten legs, the top of which are very large pincers.

Often used to represent lobster as food as well as in connection to the US state of Maine.

In its release year of 2018, Emojipedias original sample image was criticized as anatomically incorrect but was shortly after resolved. That year, the transgender community embraced the lobster as a symbol for their efforts for Transgender Flagemoji.

Samsung, WhatsApp, and Facebooks lobsters are depicted at an angle.

name: Lock
description:
A locked (closed) padlock, as used to secure a latch or chain, or as an icon for a secure internet connection, private account, or locked device. Generally depicted with a gold base and silver shackle. WhatsApps design is silver.

Commonly used for content concerning safety, security, privacy, and protection as well as various senses of lock, e.g., locked in/down.

This emoji does not display in page titlesonApples Safari web browser, presumably to prevent less reputable sites from pretending to be secure (encrypted using HTTPS).

Additionally, this emoji is not supported in Twitter / X names,to minimize confusion with private accounts on the platform. Learn more here.

See also: üîè Locked With Pen and üîê Locked With Key.

name: Lock with Ink Pen

A locked (closed) padlock with a fountain pen or nib positioned at various angles in front of it.Vendors implement the same design as their üîí Locked and the same or similar design as their üñãÔ∏è Fountain Pen or ‚úíÔ∏è Black Nib.

May represent digital certificates in public-key technology. May also have similar applications as üîí Locked (privacy, security) and üñãÔ∏è Fountain Pen or ‚úíÔ∏è Black Nib (writing, signing).

Apples design previously displayed a nib, as didGoogles.

This emoji does not display in page titlesonApples Safari web browser, presumably to prevent less reputable sites from pretending to be secure (encrypted using HTTPS).

Additionally, this emoji is not supported in Twitter / X names,to minimize confusion with private accounts on the platform. Learn more here.

name: Lollipop

A colorful lollipop made of swirled hard candy attached to a stick. Colors vary by platform, though most designs show rainbow colors or pinks and reds.

This emoji tends to spike in use around Halloween.

Samsung, Microsoft, and Facebook all used to have pink and red designs, but have since opted for rainbow colors.

name: Long Drum
description:
A long drum with a tall body and a cylindrical or hourglass shell. Can be used to represent various drums found around the world from Africa to the Caribbean to Latin America to Asia. Types of long drum include (but are not limited to) djembe, talking drum, conga, bongo, tumbadora, atabaque, and dhol.

Can also be used to talk about drums, music, or beats in general.

name: Lotion Bottle
description:
A bottle of lotion for the skin, such as moisturizer or sunscreen (sunblock). May be used for other hygienic liquids, including shampoo and body wash, as well as beauty products.

Appearance varies across platforms, but commonly depicted in white and gold colors. Some designs also include a dropleticon on the bottle.

Mostplatforms feature a bottle with a pump, though others previously displayeda cylinder with a cap.

name: Lotus

A pink lotus flower in full bloom.

Apple and Twitterfeature the same designs as their ‚úíÔ∏èBlack Nib, but with their tips angled to the lower left.

A suitcase or bag, as used for traveling. Most platforms depict gray or blue rolling luggage with an extended handle. Commonly used for various content concerning traveling or taking trips, whether for business or leisure.

Apples design features an old-fashioned, leather, trunk-styled case with graphic luggage labels/stickers, not to be confused with üíºBriefcase or üëúHandbag. Google and Facebook also include such stickers.

description:
A yellow face with raised eyebrows, enlarged eyes, slight frown, and long nose,indicatingits telling a lie in the manner of Pinocchio. Like that character, Facebooks design features a wooden nose.

May represent lying, a liar, and other concepts of deceit and dishonesty to varying degrees of intensity. Sometimes used to convey disbelief (e.g., You must be kidding) or feeling abashed (e.g., as ifcaught in the act of lying).

description: Aribbon and medallion generallyawardedto aperson in the military for heroic acts.

name: Milky Way
description:
The Milky Way  a galaxy ofbillions of stars that includesour ownsolar system and planet earth.

Shown by many platforms as a night sky, with silhouettes of mountains or hills in the foreground.

name: Minibus
description: A small bus or minivandesigned to carry fewer people than a full-sized bus. Displayed in white on most platforms(green on Facebook).

name: Minidisc
description:
A minidisc, depicted as a small, silver or gold optical disc housed in a square cartridge, its shutter positioned to the right.

Discontinued as an audio and data storage format in 2013 due to the success of CD and MP3 technology, though the emoji is commonly used to represent CDs, DVDs, and related film and music content, especially albums.

Samsungs design previously featured a silver disc labeled MD, for minidisc. Early designs from au by KDDI showed an angled üíæ Floppy Disk, perhaps as being inserted or ejected into a computer drive.

See also üíø Optical Disc andüìÄ DVD.

name: Mirror
description:
A mirror with an ornate gold or silver frame. The shape and style of the mirror varies from platform to platform.

Used to talk about mirrors, reflection, or self-reflection.

name: Mirror Ball
description: A mirror ball, also calleda disco ball. A hanging spheremade up of a bunch of tiny mirrors, which reflect spots oflight around a room, creating a party atmosphere.

name: Mobile Phone
description:
A mobile phone (cell phone), as used to text, check social media, or take selfies. Depicted as a black or gray smartphone with a generic blue screen or multicolored app icons. Commonly used for various content concerning mobile phones, technology, and communication.

The designs from Apple, Google, Microsoft, and Samsung resemble phones offered by their respective companies, e.g., iPhone. WhatsApps design features a night sky as its wallpaper, displaying the time as 9:34.

Early designs for the mobile phone emoji from au by KDDI resembled a traditionaltelephone receiver, and vice versa, before having their codepoints swapped in later releases.

See also üì≤Mobile Phone With Arrow.

name: Mobile Phone Off
description:
A sign indicating that mobile phones should be turned off. Used insituations such as a cinema or live performance.

Displayed as a mobile phone with the word OFF. Previously shown with a cross instead of the word OFF on Windows.

name: Mobile Phone with Rightwards Arrow at Left
description:
A mobile phone (cell phone) with a rightwardarrow pointed at it from the left. Intended to indicate an incoming call or message, but used to represent mobile phones, technology, and communication more generally.

Arrow color varies, but is often blue. Vendors implement the same design as üì± Mobile Phone.

name: Money Bag
description:
A bag full of money. Depicted as a sack, usually tan, tied off and displaying a dollar sign. May be filled with coins, as most platforms show a rounded bag.

Commonly used for various content concerning wealth and money.

name: Money-Mouth Face
description:
A yellow face with raised eyebrows, currency symbols for eyes (usuallydollar signs), and an open smile sticking out a tongue (usually colored green with a dollar sign, echoing adollar banknote).

Facebooks design shows this emojisdollar signeyes over a gray coin shape, whileHuaweis emoji design has yen-shaped eyes instead ofdollar signs.

Used for a wide range of content dealing with money, including making money, loving wealth, being or feeling rich, and concepts of success and excellence (e.g.,on themoney).

name: Money with Wings
description: A banded stack of U.S. dollar bills with feather wings, as if flying. Its flight may represent losing, transferring, or earning money, but commonly used for wealth, money, and success more generally, often with aflourish or sense of flair.

name: Monkey
description:
A monkey, a small primate with long limbs and tail for climbing trees. Generally depicted as a cartoon-styled, brown monkey with a cheeky facial expression, shown in full profile facingleft, sitting on its hind legs with a long, curled tail and round ears.

As with üêµ Monkey Face, often used with a playful tone or for metaphorical senses of monkey.

One of the 12 animals of the Chinese zodiac.

WhatsApps monkey is facing right, Facebooks has shaggy hair.

This emoji is considered racist in some contexts, particularly when used to disparage, insult, and abuse people with dark skin, especially Black people.

name: Monkey Face
description:
A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a monkey, looking straight ahead. Depicted as a brown-haired monkey with a tan or pinkish face, round ears, nostrils, and open-mouthed grin.

As with the full-bodied üêí Monkey, often used with a playful tone or for metaphorical senses of monkey.

One of the 12 animals of the Chinese zodiac. Available as an Apple Animoji.

Vendors implement the sameor similar monkey face in their Three Wise Monkeys emojis: üôà See-No-Evil Monkey, üôâ Hear-No-Evil Monkey, andüôä Speak-No-Evil Monkey.

Facebooks monkey previously resembled üêª Bear Face.

This emoji is considered racist in some contexts, particularly when used to disparage, insult, and abuse people with dark skin, especially Black people.

name: Monorail
description: Similar to a train, but running on a single track.¬†Monorails are often found at theme parks, or other tourist destinations.

name: Moon Cake
description: The round, golden-brown pastry of a Chinese mooncake, a traditional delicacy and lunar symbol of the Mid-Autumn Festival. Many platforms feature a design or character imprinted on the crust, and depict a slice cut out to show a brown paste with a duck egg yolk inside. Twitter displays the Chinese character for fall/autumn or harvest (Áßã) on top.

name: Moon Viewing Ceremony
description:
Moon Viewing Ceremonies (called Tsukimi in Japan) are held each year in autumn to celebrate the full moon and waxing moon in¬†Japan.
This symbol¬†shows Japanese pampas grass and dango (sweet dessert food) which are used in the ceremony, as well as the moon in the background.

name: Moose
description:
A moose head with large antlers.

Can be used to talk about the actual animal. Can also be used to represent countries including Canada and Sweden, where the moose is considered a national symbol. Can also be used alongside the phrase cool as a moose.

Googles Moose is facing left, while Twitter displays a full-bodied moose

name: Mosque
description: A mosque building, a place of worship for followers of Islam. Shown with a domed roof and a minaret.

name: Mosquito
description:
A mosquito, a type of bloodsucking fly. Depicted as a brown or black mosquito on its six, long legs, with wings, long abdomen, and needle-like mouth. Variously shown from above or facing left.

May be used to represent various insects, other bugs and bug bites, and insect-borne diseases (e.g., malaria). May also be used for metaphorical pests.

Facebooks mosquitohas a red abdomen, as if filled with blood.

name: Mother Christmas
description: Mother Christmas, more commonly known as Mrs. Claus, is the wife of Santa Claus.Displayed as an older womanwith glassesanda festive red and white bonnet.See also: Christmas emoji list.

name: Motor Boat
description: A small boat powered by an engine. Also known as aspeedboat or powerboat.

name: Motor Scooter
description: A motor scooter, which may be displayed as any type of motorbike with or without a step-through frame. Distinct from the racing motorcycle, which is used for sport, not transport.

name: Motorized Wheelchair
description:
A motorized wheelchair. Most platforms show a red and black or blue and black wheelchair. Distinct from ‚ôø Wheelchair Symbol which is used as signage to indicate accessible facilities.See also üë©ü¶ºWoman in MotorizedWheelchair or üë®ü¶ºMan in Motorized Wheelchair.

ü¶Ω Manual Wheelchair was approved at the same time as this emoji.

name: Motorway
description: A wide road shown from a first person perspective. Apples artwork displays a road sign to Curpertino.

name: Mount Fuji
description:
Mount Fuji (calledFuji-san in Japan) is the largest mountain in Japan. Often seen with snow on the peak in colder months of the year.

It is considered lucky in Japan to dream of Mt Fuji in the first dream of the new year.

name: Mountain
description: A mountain shown with two peaks and blue sky. Similar to the snow capped mountain emoji.

name: Mountain Bicyclist
description: A person (cyclist) who rides a mountain bike: a type of off-road bicycle.Intended to be gender-neutral.

name: Mountain Cableway
description: A cable car transportation system allowing users to swiftly ascend up a mountain.Can also be used as a tourist attraction, or as a form of public transport.

name: Mountain Railway
description:
A train and railway in themountains.

Previously displayed asa funicular in Microsofts artwork. Android also previously displayedthis train as front-facing andleaving a tunnel, which appearedsimilarly to the metro emoji at small sizes.

name: Mouse
description:
Eek! A mouse, a small rodent with large ears and a long tail. Generally depicted in white in full profile on all fours facing left, with pink ears, feet, and tail, often with reddish eyes.

See also üê≠ Mouse Face. Not to be confused with üêÄ Rator üñ±Ô∏è Computer Mouse.

Facebooks mouse is sitting on its hind legs. Googles design waspreviously more cartoon-styled, standing on its hind legs and facing forward with a buck tooth. Microsofts mouse was previously brown.

name: Mouse Face
description:
A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a mouse, looking straight ahead. Generally depicted as a gray or white mouse face with large, round ears, a pink, pointed nose, and whiskers.

Often used with a more affectionate tone than the full-bodied üêÅ Mouse. Not to be confused with üêπ Hamster Face.

GoogleandFacebooks designs feature a mouse with buck teeth. Microsofts design was previously brown.

name: Mouse Trap
description:
A trap used to catch a mouse, rat, or other unwanted rodent.Metaphorically used in emoji form to suggest any kind of trap or entrapment.

The style of trap shown on major platforms has a box held high with a single stick. A wedge of cheese is used to lure a mouse into the box, knocking the stick away and trapping  but not killing  the mouse.

This is distinct from other traps which kill or injure upon capture.

name: Mouth
description:
Ahuman mouth which isgenerally displayed as a pair oflips and a top row of teeth, instead of the inside of themouth.

May be used to indicate the spoken wordor as an alternative to Kiss Mark.

Notably used alongside twoeye emojis to create the It is what it is emoji face: üëÅÔ∏èüëÑüëÅÔ∏è. Learn more here.

name: Movie Camera
description:
A classic movie camera. Depicted as a black camera with two mounted reels of film, viewfinder, and lens pointed left or right.

Commonly used for various content concerning movies, film, and video as well as an icon for a video, as before an upload, link, or credit. May also be used in relation to the 2017Emoji Movie.

Facebooks design previously resembled a video camera mounted on a tripod.

Not to be confused with üìΩÔ∏è Film Projector.

name: Moyai
description:
A moai, one of the famed, giant stone statues of human figureson Easter Island. Depicted as a graystone carving of a stylized human head with a prominent brow and nose, most often facing left.

Sometimes used for various idiosyncratic purposes, such as conveying a stoic, deadpan, or silly expression. For example, this emoji is often used to represent various sigma or chad memes due to its chiselled emotionaless features.

Its official Unicode name of Moyaiand inclusion in early Japanese emoji sets, such as from au by KDDI, suggestthe emoji may represent the Moyai Statue near Shibuya Station in Tokyo, Japan; previous designs from Google and Microsoftresemble the Tokyo statue. Other Tokyo landmarks are represented inüóºTokyo Tower and, formerly, Shibuya 109.

Showing white and black keys, this keyboard is played by a pianist to make music. Commonly used as a piano emoji.

Displays as two eighth-notes (quavers in British English) connected with a beam. A single eight-note (quaver) was previously used in Microsoft andGooglesemoji designs.

description:
A person, generally depicted as being older with gray hair,wearing a red Christmas (aka Santa) hat. Does not represent any specific character in folklore. Mx Clausprovides agender inclusive alternative toüéÖSanta Claus orü§∂Mrs. Claus.

Apple depicts Mx Claus as wearing glasses, while other vendors do not.

Mx is anhonorific that does not indicate gender.

name: Nail Polish

Colored nail polish being applied to finger nails, oftenusedtodisplay an air ofnonchalance or indifference.

Shown asred, pink or purple nail polish on most platforms, the color rarely changes the meaning of this emoji. Previously displayed as a single bottle of nail polish on Android and on Windows.

A name badge, used to identify oneself in a location that others may not know your name, such as a school trip, or a work conference.

Thistulip-shapedname badge is one of many designs commonly foundat kindergartens in Japan.

name: National Park
description: A national park, generally displayed with mountains, a river or stream, and trees.

name: Nauseated Face
description:
A sickly-green face with concerned eyes and puffed, often red cheeks, as if holding back vomit. May represent physical illness or general disgust. Not to be confused with ü§Æ Face Vomiting.

Differs from other smileys conveying sickness, including ü§í Face With Thermometer (used especially for colds and flus) and ü§ï Face With Head-Bandage (physical injury).

name: Nazar Amulet
description:
A nazar, an eye-shaped amulet believed to protect against the evil eye, especially in Turkish culture. Depicted as a rich blue, circular bead with a black dot in the center ringed with white and light blue, resembling an eye.

Commonly used to represent eyes, various senses of looking, various senses ofcharms, envy and jealousy, andTurkey and Turkish culture. Also used for its blue color more generally.

WhatsApp, Facebook, and Huaweis designs include a small hole, as for threading the amulet on a string or chain.

Note: this emoji is not supported in Twitter / X names,to minimize confusion with a verified checkmark. Learn more here.

name: Necktie
description:
A necktie commonly wornat work or formal occasions, usually shown being worn with a shirt.

Colors and patterns for both the necktie and the shirtvary by platform.

Previous designs from Google, Facebook, and Samsung displayed a necktie on its own.

description: A cross mark that displays with a white outlined appearance. Shows on most platforms with a bright green rounded rectangle or circle surrounding it.

description:
A symbol representing Blood Type B.Displayed as the letter Bon a red background.

Sometimes used online to replace the letter C at the start of wordsin reference to the Bloods street gangs practiceof turning words like coolintobool. This has expanded in some instances to starting any word with the letter B, or more specifically, this emoji which makes it moreüÖ±Ô∏èlear that a letter has been replaced.

name: Negative Squared Latin Capital Letter O
description: A symbol representing Blood Type O.Displayed as the letter Oon a red background.

name: Negative Squared Latin Capital Letter P
description:
Depicted by major emoji vendors as blue square with a white letter P contained within it. Most often to represent a parking space or parking lot.

As of early 2022this emoji has frequently been used as a positiveresponse on social media - thats üÖøÔ∏è. This is due to anassociation with the song Pushing P by American rapperGunna.

name: Nerd Face
description:
A smiling yellow face with glasses, often with teeth showing, originally buck teeth on most platforms.

While this emoji is often used by people calling themselves nerds in a self-deprecating way, the nerdy glasses paired with buck teeth can, and often does, evoke anti-Asian stereotypes. The fact that the default color of emoji faces is yellow further pushes this emoji into racist yellowfaceterritory.

Some platforms have redesigned nerd faceover time to not have buck teeth, perhaps in acknowledgement of the harm this imagerymay cause. Google, Facebook, WhatsApp, and JoyPixels originally featured designs with buck teeth but have since changed (or completely removed) the teeth on nerd face.

Apple, Twitter, Microsoft, Samsung, and other platforms still use designs for this emoji that include buck teeth.

name: Nest with Eggs
description:
A birds nest with eggs inside.

May be used to talk about actual nests or birds. May also be used to talk about home in general or to represent phrases like nest egg or empty nest.

ü™π Empty Nest was approved at the same time asNest with Eggs.

name: Nesting Dolls
description: Nesting dolls,also called matryoshka dolls or Russian dolls, decorated with bright colors including red, yellow, blue, and green. Allplatforms depict the nesting dolls as open, revealing smaller dolls within the bases of larger dolls. Dolls are all decorated with womenwearingheadscarfs. Some platforms show a flower motif on the womens dresses or aprons.

name: Neutral Face
description: A yellow face with simple, open eyes and a flat, closed mouth. Intended to depict a neutral sentiment but often used to convey mild irritation and concern or a deadpan sense of humor.

name: New Moon Symbol
description:
A new moon, the first of the eight phases of the moon. Depicts the moon as a full, bluish- or grayish-black, cratered disc, not illuminated by the sun.

May be used to represent the moon more generally, nighttime, outer space, andastronomy. May also be used to convey enchanting or eerie feelings.

See also üåöNew Moon Face. Used as part of the Moon Emoji Creep meme.

Googles new moon was previouslya gray circle with a yellow outline. Samsungs design once resembled a full moon with stars and previously displayed as a new moon in a night sky with stars.

name: New Moon with Face
description:
A new moon with a smiling face, as the Man in the Moon. Generally depicts the moon as a dark disc with a slightly smiling human face and nose.

See also üåëNew Moon.May be used to represent the moon more generally. Popularly perceived as creepy, used to throw shade (express disapproval), or convey various suggestive or ironic sentiments.

Apple and WhatsApps eyes are looking left, as if giving the side-eye. Samsung and Facebooks faces are looking straight ahead. Googles facial expression resembles üòèSmirking Face, Twitters üôÇSlightly Smiling Face.

Googles face previously evoked Lenny Face, Microsofts eyes appeared closed, and Facebooks face was a simple smiley.

The front page of a newspaper, as people once read the news before the internet. Commonly used for various content concerning news, media, and journalism as well as personal news.

Most platforms depict a nondescript masthead, images, and columns of text. Apples newspaper is called The Apple Times, featuring a logo based on itsü¶Ö Eagle and a picture of its üåã Volcano. Facebooks is called Daily Feed, with a headline El Capitan and picture of that famous rock formation in Yosemite National Park. WhatsApps paper reads Daily News with a picture of a map.

See also üóûÔ∏è Rolled-Up Newspaper.

A person dressed as a ninja with a black hood, a mask covering the lower half of their face, and the hilt of a knife or swordemerging from behind their shoulder.

The now-discontinued MicrosoftZWJ sequenceüê±üë§Ninja Catdid not include theninjaemoji at all as it was developed several years before ninjawas approved. It combinedüê± Cat Face and üë§ Bust in Silhouette and wasonly available from Microsoft prior to the debut of the Fluent emoji set in November 2021.

A bicycle with a red stroke through it, indicatingthat bikes are prohibited from this location.

A red circle with a diagonal line through the middle, from top-left to bottom right, used toindicate that something is not permitted

Commonly shown in conjunction with other symbols to indicateNo Smoking, No Bikes, or similar.

name: No Mobile Phones

The number eighteen with a red stroke through it, indicating a location where a person must be aged 18 or above to enter. Often used online to indicate adult or NSFW content.

Googles design includes the text under above thenumber eighteen.

The Samsung version of this emoji previously displayedthe number 19. This may have beendue to thepractice ofcountingthe first year of life asone instead ofzeroin parts of East Asia suchasSouth Korea(the location of the Samsung Headquarters).

A pedestrian symbol with a red stroke through it, indicatingthat pedestrians are prohibited from this location.

May be seen in dedicated bike lanes, highways, or other areas not suitable to be on-foot.

name: No Smoking Symbol

name: Non-Potable Water Symbol

A water tap with a red stroke through it, indicatingthat water is not safe for drinking (non-potable).

May be used at a camp site or other area that has water suitable for cleaning or other non-drinking purposes.

A dark-colored, hardcovernotebook, as used to write or take notes in school. Commonly used for various content concerning writing and schooling.

Several platforms, including Apple, feature a cover with black-and-white marbling, evoking a classic composition book used in the U.S. Apples design displays Notes on its cover. Google, Microsoft, and Samsungs covers were previously yellow or brown.

name: Notebook with Decorative Cover
description:
A closed, hardcover notebook, as used for journaling or sketching. Appearance varies across platforms, with most designs featuring relatively plain covers. Commonly used for content concerning writing and schooling.

Apples cover is tan and labelled Notes.Facebooks design is most decorative, pink with a flower pattern.

Googles design was previouslygray and features different-colored tabs, while Samsungs previously displayed the easteregg initials SJST.

A metal bolt with a nut threaded around it, as by a wrench. Often positioned at a 45 angle, the head of the bolt at the upper left. Commonly used for various content concerning tools, building, and construction. May also be used for other hardware, including screws.

Apples bolt previously resembleda screw, Googlesa dumbbell; Microsofts design previously featured the nut and bolt separately.

A red, octagonal sign, often but not always shown with a white or grey rim. Used in many countries as a stop sign.

Unlike other platforms,Huaweis design for this emoji displays the word STOP.

An octopus, a sea animal with eight legs, known to change color and releaseink. Generally depicted as a pink or orange octopus facing forward, with a large, round head, prominent eyes, and its tentacle-like arms raised at its sides. Platforms vary in the number of arms shown, ranging from four to the full eight, with several designs featuring suckers on them.

Not to be confused with ü¶ë Squid, though their applications may overlap.

Twitters octopus is purple. Apples has a friendly, cartoon-styled appearance. Google and Samsungs octopuses previously looked surprised, while Microsoftssuggested an üëæ Alien Monster.

Often served as a stew or skewered and dipped into soy sauce. Resembles theDangoand may be used for other skewered foods (e.g., shishkebab, roasting marshmallows) or spears.

name: Office Building

A generic, high-rise office building. Generally found in cities, and most active during business hours.

The office building shown in Twemoji 2.0 is of Twitter HQ in San Fransisco.

A barrel for transporting bulk liquids, such as oil. Generally depicted as a red or blue metal drum with holes or a stopper on its lid. Commonly used for various content concerning petroleum or hazardous waste.

Googles design previouslydisplayeda yellow oil drop symbol, whileSamsungs design previouslyfeatured a yellow hazard sign.

This can also be used asasymbol of White Supremacy, depending on context.

Like üîë Key, often used figuratively, e.g., the key to success, being key(crucial). May also be applied to antiques.

This emoji does not display in page titlesonApples Safari web browser, presumably to prevent less reputable sites from pretending to be secure (encrypted using HTTPS).

A curbside mailbox (letterbox, postbox) with its signal flag lowered and its slot empty. Generally depicted in blue or gray with a red flag.Used for various content concerning postal deliveries and email.

Indicates in the United States that there is outgoing mail (post) for pickup. May also indicate that incoming mail has been delivered.

An orangutan, the orange-haired ape with long arms. Depicted facing forward, with a long broad faceand sitting with its legs bent. Occasionally shown scratching its head. Color varies across platforms, ranging from orangeto light brown.

An otter, the playful water mammal in the weasel family. Depicted as a light-brown otter on its back, with its forepaws held together and whiskered face to the left, generally with its long tail curled up.

May be used to refer to certain members of the LGBTQ community, a la the slang term otter.

Apples otter is in water, holding a stone, as is Microsofts.

name: Outbox Tray

A paper tray with an up arrow on top, as a symbol for an email outbox. Generally depicted as a white or wooden tray with a red arrow pointing upwards. Facebooks design contains paper.

May be used for various digital activity, including uploading, messaging, emailing, ordering, and sharing.

Googles design previously featureda blue arrow and containedpaper.Samsungs arrow was previously green.

A reddish-orange face with furrowed eyebrows, tongue stuck out, and beads of sweat, as if overheated from high temperatures. Number and position of sweat droplets vary by platforms. May also represent physical attractiveness (slang, hot).

Most platforms feature expressions that are variations on üò∞ Anxious Face With Sweat or üò• Sad but Relieved Face.

An owl, the hooting, large-eyed bird. Depicted as a brown owl with its headfacing forward.Shown with large, round, gold-rimmed eyes, talons, tucked wings, andhorn-like tufts of feathers.

May be used to represent wisdom. Once popularly used in connection with the hip-hop artist Drake.

Microsofts owl previously resembled a barn owl, Samsungs was purple.

name: Ox

An ox, a bovine used as a draft animal. Depicted in brown in full profile on all fours facing left, with a tail and short horns.

One of the 12 animals of the Chinese zodiac. Often used to represent ‚ôâ Taurus (the Bull) in the Western zodiac. 2021 is Year of the Ox.

Often used to represent a bull and occasionally paired with üí© Pile of Poo to stand in for slang terms.Not to be confused with üêÉ Water Buffalo.

name: Oyster

name: Package

A package (parcel), as contains items ordered online. Depicted at various angles as a light-brown, cardboard box, with a shipping label and its top taped shut.

Commonly used for content concerning shipping, delivery, and moving as well as for boxes more generally.

Apples design features an image of a wine glass, indicating fragile contents, and this way up orientation arrows. It wasbrieflyidentical to its üéÅ Wrapped Gift.

name: Page Facing Up
description:
A white piece of paper, its top right corner curled or dog-eared, with text printed on it, as a business letter or icon for a document on a computer. Commonly used for content concerning various types of documents and writing.

Most platforms indicate text with dark lines. Apples design features an easter egg, addressed Dear Katie and signed Take care from John Appleseed with the text of its 19972002 Crazy Ones/Think Different ad campaign:

Heres to the crazy ones. The misfits. The rebels. The troublemakers. The round pegs in the square holes. The ones who see things differently. Theyre not fond of rules. You can quote them, disagree with them, glorify or vilify them. About the only thing you cant do is ignore them. Because they change things. They push the human race forward. And while some may see them as the crazy ones, we see genius. Because the ones who are crazy enough to think that they can change the world, are the ones who do.

Early designs from au by KDDI show a slanted document, suggesting this emoji may have been originally intended to represent adigital document being sent electronically.

Not to be confused with üìÉ Page With Curl or other emojis featuring sheets of paper.

name: Page with Curl
